=1> NToV Etiquette                                                     <br>
                                                                   <br>
A Guild must kill Aaroynar to join the Rotation.                   <br>
                                                                   <br>
NToV is a multiple day zone.  Once a Guild/Entity enters the zone  and kills Aaroynar, NToV is theirs until the last dragon is dead.                                                                 <br>
<br>
If a Guild trying to break into the Rotation fails, one of the     <br>
other Guilds in the Rotation will get &quot;ownership&quot; of the zone,    <br>
based on discussions held amongst them.  <br>
<br>
On FFA days, such as Patch Nights, a discussion is held amonst the guilds as to who would go in so the mobs aren't <br>
&quot;wasted&quot;.  The only stricture is that the next regularly scheduled guild will not go in, thereby getting 2 &quot;turns&quot;.<br>
<br>
Additional note: If NToV crashes during a normal Rotation Turn and the Rotational Guild has not finished clearing and is still in the zone, they keep &quot;possession&quot; of the zone when it's brought back up. If they choose to leave without re-clearing, it then passes to the next regularly scheduled Guild, as part of the Rotation. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/unyca.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nyca</A> at: 9/5/02 6:13:19 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/unyca.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nyca</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Singing Goddess</span><br>  Posts: 1082<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(9/16/02 11:54:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm52.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: North Temple of Veehasn</span><hr size=1> Addendum by Gromm of BotS:<br>
<br>
The basics of the ToVN Rotation:<br>
<br>
(Any reference to guild applies equally to an alliance. I just use the word 'guild' as there are currently no alliances on the ToVN rotation.)<br>
<br>
A guild's/alliance's rotational turn in ToVN starts at the instant that the guild kills the first mob from the North Wing of TOV on their raid. Any mob that spawns/lives behind the door that exits to the north from the hub area is considered to be a ToVN mob. These mobs are wyverns, drakes, hatchlings (chickens), dragons, wurms, and a few named mobs from back there. This turn lasts for 48 hours after which the guild on rotation must vacate ToVN and forfeit the remainder of the ToVN spawns to the next guild on rotation. This forfeit of mobs does not count toward the next guild's rotational turn (The next guild's rotation turn is not affected by the forfeiture of mobs by a preceding guild).<br>
<br>
All mobs that are considered North Wing Mobs are considered to be 'owned' by the guild on rotation for their turn. These include, but are not limited to, Ikatair, Eashen, (the other named wyvern that drops nothing), and all named guards, in addition to the 'normal' mobs that spawn there.<br>
<br>
Initially, the rotation was like other mobs in that the rotational guild had 48 hours from spawn time to clear all the dragons. This was when there was no random component in the spawn times. When the random spawning was put in for ToVN, the guilds on rotation unanimously chose to change the rotational agreement to allow for the 'drift' in spawn times over time. Over a few weeks of non-interrupted EQ play, the spawn times of the dragons can be spread out over a large period of time - longer than 48 hours for sure. By the original terms of the agreement, this would make it impossible for a rotational guild to be able to attempt some dragons sometimes because they wouldn't have spawned. It was agreed that a guild may postpone their start of ToVN until they are sure that all the dragons have spawned, thus enabling them to theoretically attempt all the dragons there during their 48 hour turn. However, some time limit has to be placed on this extention. The rotation guild has to start within 24 hours of when all the dragons are known to be spawned. A rotational guild may forego this postponement and start ToVN at any time they wish on their turn. However, this guild is required to forfeit any spawns that happen after their 48 hour turn to the next guild on rotation.<br>
<br>
Each guild gets a 48 hour turn to kill all the dragons that have spawned on their turn. The forfeiture of dragons by a previous guild does not change this (basically, if you forfeit dragons, you give the next guild on rotation free dragons).<br>
<br>
To get on the ToVN rotation, you simply kill Aaryonyar, the 'gate keeper' of the ToVN dragons. He isn't the hardest dragon, just simply one that you really have no choice in killing since he resides at the T intersection of the area where the other dragons live. Note that 'sniping' Ikatair and Eashen and then suiciding on Aaryonyar so that your guild can claim they were simply unsuccessful in entering the rotation is considered a 'bad thing'. <br>
